Zoom appearances.
Defendant in custody at Manitowoc County Jail.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of two (2) years.  That is one (1) year initial confinement followed by one (1) year extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence imposed on 20 CF 816.
The defendant is eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
The defendant has credit for 55 days.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2)	AODA assessment and follow through;
3)	Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, treatment, work search or combination;
4)	Pay court costs;
5)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6)	maintain absolute sobriety;
7)	Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.
Minutes.

Zoom appearances.
The State moves to delete the repeater enhancer on count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1, felony bail jumping.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1)	AODA assessment and follow through;
2)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3)	Pay court costs;
4)	pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5)	provide DNA sample;
6)	maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
7)	maintain absolute sobriety;
8)	Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.
If revoked, the defendant has credit of 4 days.
Cash bail to be applied to court costs.
(court paperwork mailed to defendant at 1807 Madison Street, Two Rivers, WI)
Minutes.


